The rkt binary and stage1 images provided in this tarball should be
usable immediately after unpacking. rkt will use stage1-coreos.aci
from this directory by default as a fallback. The steps below will
make rkt more usable though (like making rkt available to everyone on
the system, enabling rkt fetch for non-root users, integrating it with
systemd, making rkt's --stage1-from-dir usable, etc).

1. copy rkt to /usr/bin
  - cp rkt /usr/bin
2. add a rkt group
  - groupadd rkt
3. add users to the group
  - gpasswd -a ${USER} rkt
  - newgrp rkt
4. create data directories
  - ./scripts/setup-data-dir.sh
5. install tmpfiles
  - cp init/systemd/tmpfiles.d/rkt.conf /usr/lib/tmpfiles.d/
6. install unit files and reload systemd
  - cp init/systemd/*.{service,socket,timer} /usr/lib/systemd/system
  - systemctl daemon-reload
7. install the stage1 ACIs
  - mkdir -p /usr/lib/rkt/stage1-images
  - cp *.aci /usr/lib/rkt/stage1-images
8. install bash completion
  - cp bash_completion/rkt.bash /etc/bash_completion.d
9. probably disable SELinux (this may be unnecessary, please test rkt first before following it)
  - setenforce Permissive
  - sed -i'' 's/enforcing/permissive/' /etc/selinux/config
